title: An Introduction to the Hirshhorn Museum
description:
An Introduction to the Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden, Smithsonian Institution
Harry N. Abrams | 1974 | ISBN: 0810920514 | English | 82 pages | PDF | 16 MB

Displays the art of our time in the celebrated Gordon Bunshaft designed cylindrical building and adjoining plaza and sunken sculpture garden. Highlights In-depth collection of modern masters and works by emerging artists; cutting-edge films; sculptures by Rodin, Matisse, and Moore on the plaza and in the garden
